        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">DoTs should do full damage on a boss mob because it typically doesn't move much during a fight, particularly if it can summon. Only if it chases someone who over aggroed would the mob be moving.</P><P>I think the 18 secs was mentioned because that was the amount they increased the duration of DoTs by way back when this patch went live (Sep 99 remember). </P><P>So if mobs moves for 18 secs your dot did the same as the old duration (as if those extra 18 secs weren't there). If it moves for less than 18 your getting part of that bonus time applied hence more damage. If it moves more than 18 secs its less damage because it's using up even more of the spell duration.</P><P>The bit I'm uncertain about is where it says if the mob is moving when the damage is applied it takes 66% damage. Does this mean that as long the mob is stationary on the 6th second of the tick it takes full? Conversely if it moves for 1 sec every tick but that happens to coincide with the end of the tick will it constantly take less damage?</P><P>More importantly does this patch message even still apply? Is this how it still works in the game 2 years later?</P><P>Narben the Gnomish Gnecro<BR>"Find your own damn witty comment"<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
