        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I can't claim to know the actual code, however, this was what discussions with Verant came up with after the patch.</P><P>Mob BEING moved is different than mob moving.  In other words, the only movement that counts for this 1/3 reduction in damage on dots is if the mobs feet are moving and he's trying to get a target.  If it's being pushed, either by spells or melee damage or if he running away for any reason, full damage applies.</P><P></P><P>Therros Rex'Necri<BR>53 Tier'Dal Necromancer<BR>< Kel'Daoine > of Tarew Marr<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
